  <mads:note type="source">His Libanii Opera recensuit R. Foerster, 1903</mads:note>
  <mads:note type="source">Enc. Brit., c1972: v. 13, p. 1016 (Libanius (314-393); Greek sophist
        and rhetorician, whose orations and letters are a major source for the political, social,
        and economic life of Antioch and of the eastern part of the Roman empire in the 4th cent.,
        was born at Antioch, capital of Syria)</mads:note>
